[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software architecture and design
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Architecture and Design phase for the software
element of the railway control and protection system identified below.
It is prepared in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.3 (Architecture
and design), and collects six output deliverables from Table A.1:

   9. Software Architecture Specification
  10. Software Design Specification
  11. Software Interface Specifications
  12. Software Integration Test Specification
  13. Software/Hardware Integration Test Specification
  14. Software Architecture and Design Verification Report

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (doc 9, 10, 12, 13, 14): BASIC=R, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.1 (doc 11, interface specifications): BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.3 (architecture techniques): values vary per technique.
- Table A.4 (design and implementation techniques): values vary per technique.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: SAD-xxx (requirements) and SWIT-xxx / HWIT-xxx
  (integration test cases).
- Duplicate SAD-050/051/052 for each software module.
- Duplicate SWIT-001/HWIT-001 entries for each integration test case.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

