[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-013
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Architecture modelling
STATEMENT: >>>
Architectural models shall be used to describe the software structure and
behaviour at the component level. The following modelling notations shall
be applied as appropriate to the design:

  - Component and connector diagrams (e.g. UML component or SysML BDD/IBD)
    showing modules, interfaces, and data flows.
  - Deployment diagrams showing the mapping of software to hardware.
  - State machine diagrams for modules with complex reactive behaviour.
  - Sequence / timing diagrams for safety-critical interaction sequences.

Models shall be:
  a) Consistent with the textual architecture description in SAD-010/SAD-011.
  b) Subject to the same version control as the SAS.
  c) Verified for consistency with the SRS (SAD-090).
  d) Used as input to detailed design (section 3) and interface specifications
     (section 4).

Modelling tool: <tool name and version>
<<<
