[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Data flow and control flow

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-020
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Data flow specification
STATEMENT: >>>
The architecture shall define all data exchanged between software modules.
A data dictionary shall be maintained as part of the SAS baseline and shall
specify for each data item:

  Data item        | Type   | Range / valid values | Producer  | Consumer(s)
  -----------------|--------|----------------------|-----------|---------------
  <DataItem_1>     | <type> | <min..max / enum>    | <MOD-01>  | <MOD-02>
  <DataItem_2>     | <type> | <min..max / enum>    | <MOD-03>  | <MOD-01>

Shared data accessed by more than one task shall be identified and a mutual
exclusion mechanism specified (e.g. disabling of interrupts, semaphore,
double-buffer copy). The mechanism shall be described in SAD-021.

Data flow across partition boundaries (safety to non-safety or vice versa)
shall be explicitly identified and the measures taken to prevent interference
shall be described.
<<<
BASIC: R
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Analysis
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.3 – Architecture and design.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-021
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Control flow and task scheduling
STATEMENT: >>>
The architecture shall define the control flow structure of the software,
including the task model and scheduling policy. The following shall be
specified:

  Task name       | Type        | Period / trigger | Priority | Stack (bytes)
  ----------------|-------------|------------------|----------|---------------
  <Safety_Task>   | Cyclic      | <n> ms           | Highest  | <n>
  <Comms_Task>    | Event       | <message recv>   | High     | <n>
  <Diag_Task>     | Cyclic      | <n> ms           | Medium   | <n>
  <NonSafety_Task>| Background  | Idle             | Lowest   | <n>

Scheduling policy: <fixed-priority preemptive / cooperative / rate-monotonic>
RTOS / kernel: <name, version>

Critical regions protecting shared data (from SAD-020) shall be identified
and their maximum duration bounded. The impact on worst-case response times
for higher-priority tasks shall be analysed (priority inversion analysis).
Interrupt latency and interrupt service routine (ISR) execution time shall
be bounded and documented.
<<<
