[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-043
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Suitable programming languages
STATEMENT: >>>
The programming language(s) used for safety-related software shall be
suitable for the required SIL and shall support the verification methods
applied. The following shall be specified and justified:

  Language:         <Language name and version standard, e.g. C99 / C11>
  Standard:         <ISO/IEC reference>
  Justification:    <Why this language is suitable for the target SIL>
  Subset applied:   <Coding standard / language restriction — reference SAD-041>
  Compiler:         <Vendor, version — subject to tool qualification SP-082>
  Compiler flags:   <Warning level, optimisation level, ABI settings>

The language subset (SAD-041) shall be defined such that all used language
features have well-defined behaviour under the applicable language standard.
Implementation-defined and undefined behaviour shall be prohibited by the
coding standard and enforced by static analysis.

For mixed-language software (e.g. C and assembler): the boundary between
language domains shall be formally specified and the interface shall be
verified to be safe.
<<<
