[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Interface Specifications

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Interface Specifications as required
by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.3 and Table A.1 (document 11). All internal
software-to-software interfaces and software-to-hardware interfaces shall
be fully defined such that no undefined or implementation-assumed behaviour
exists at any interface boundary.
<<<

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Internal software interfaces

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-060
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fully defined internal software interfaces
STATEMENT: >>>
All internal software interfaces (function APIs, shared data structures,
message queues, and inter-task communication mechanisms) shall be fully
defined. A fully defined interface specification shall include:

  a) Interface identifier and version.
  b) Producer module and consumer module(s).
  c) Data types: precise type definition with size, endianness, and encoding.
  d) Valid value ranges or enumeration members for each field or parameter.
  e) Pre-conditions the caller must satisfy before invoking the interface.
  f) Post-conditions the provider guarantees upon return.
  g) Timing constraints: maximum latency from call to response.
  h) Error returns: all possible error codes and their meaning.
  i) Thread-safety: whether the interface is re-entrant, and the
     synchronisation mechanism used if it is not.

No interface may rely on implementation-defined behaviour, compiler-specific
assumptions, or undocumented side effects. Interfaces between SIL-classified
partitions and non-safety (SIL 0) partitions shall be explicitly identified
and verified to prevent upward interference.
<<<
BASIC: HR
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: M
SIL_4: M
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Table A.3 – Fully defined interface.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-061
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Internal interface register
STATEMENT: >>>
A register of all internal software interfaces shall be maintained as part
of the SAS/SDS baseline. The register shall include one entry per interface:

  IF ID    | Producer  | Consumer(s) | Type              | Defined in
  ---------|-----------|-------------|-------------------|------------------
  <IF-S-01>| <MOD-01>  | <MOD-02>   | Function call API | SAD-050 / header
  <IF-S-02>| <MOD-03>  | <MOD-01>   | Shared data struct| Data dictionary
  <IF-S-03>| <MOD-01>  | <MOD-05>   | Message queue     | Comms spec §<n>
  <IF-S-04>| <MOD-01>  | <MOD-06>   | Non-safety API    | Partition spec §<n>

For each interface, the "Defined in" column shall reference the design
document section or header file (under configuration management) that
contains the fully defined interface specification (SAD-060).

Changes to any interface in the register shall follow the change control
process (SP-061) and shall trigger a review of all affected modules.
<<<
