STATEMENT: >>>
All software/hardware interfaces shall be fully specified in accordance with
SAD-060 principles and with the hardware interface requirements (SRS-030).

A register of all SW/HW interfaces shall be maintained:

  IF ID     | HW component          | Driver module  | Protocol / register map
  ----------|-----------------------|----------------|------------------------
  <IF-HW-01>| <CPU watchdog timer>  | <MOD-03>       | <WDT register spec §n>
  <IF-HW-02>| <Digital I/O module>  | <MOD-03>       | <SPI driver spec §n>
  <IF-HW-03>| <NV memory>           | <MOD-03>       | <Flash driver spec §n>
  <IF-HW-04>| <Comms ASIC>          | <MOD-04>       | <UART / comms spec §n>

For each SW/HW interface, the driver or BSP module shall specify:
  a) Hardware register map or API used (reference to HW specification).
  b) Initialisation sequence and verified state on completion.
  c) Error detection and reporting (link to SAD-031).
  d) Timing: maximum delay from request to hardware response.
  e) Interrupt handling: ISR entry, exit, re-entrancy, and latency bounds.

HW specification reference: <document ID and version>
BSP / driver specification reference: <document ID or section>
<<<
