[[SECTION]]
TITLE: SW integration test strategy and test cases

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-070
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software integration test strategy
STATEMENT: >>>
Software integration testing shall verify the correct interaction between
software modules and the correct realisation of all internal interfaces
(SAD-060, SAD-061). The following strategy shall be applied:

Integration order: <top-down / bottom-up / big-bang / incremental>
Integration sequence:
  Step 1: Integrate <MOD-01> with <MOD-03>; verify SW/HW interface (SRS-030).
  Step 2: Integrate <MOD-02> with <MOD-01>; verify functional data flow.
  Step 3: Integrate <MOD-04> with <MOD-01>; verify communication interface.
  Step 4: Integrate <MOD-05> (diagnostics); verify fault injection scenarios.
  Step 5: Integrate <MOD-06> (non-safety); verify partition isolation.

Stubs and drivers: list stubs used to replace not-yet-integrated modules at
each integration step; confirm stubs do not mask real integration defects.

Test execution environment: <host / target hardware – reference SAD-072 equivalent>

Entry criteria: SAS and SDS baselined and verified (SAD-090); all module-level
tests (Level 1) passed with the required coverage (SRS-073).

Exit criteria:
  a) All integration test cases executed.
  b) All interface requirements (SAD-060, SAD-061) covered by at least one test.
  c) All Critical and Major findings resolved; residual findings assessed.
  d) Test results reviewed and approved by the Software Verifier (SP-021).
<<<
