SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.3 and Table A.1, doc 12 – SW Integration Test Specification.

[TEST_CASE]
UID: SWIT-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <Module A – Module B interface: nominal data exchange>
TEST_TYPE: Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <Module A> and <Module B> are integrated and initialised.
- Input data <DataItem_1> is set to a valid value within range [<min>..<max>].
- No fault flags are active.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Set <DataItem_1> = <nominal value>.
2. Trigger one execution cycle of <Module A>.
3. Read <output_param_1> from <Module B>'s interface.
4. Check return code from <Module B>.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- <output_param_1> equals <expected computed value> ± <tolerance>.
- Return code is OK.
- No assertions triggered; no fault log entries generated.
<<<
