[[SECTION]]
TITLE: HW-SW integration test strategy and test cases

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-080
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Software/hardware integration test strategy
STATEMENT: >>>
HW-SW integration testing shall verify that the software operates correctly
on the target hardware, including all hardware interfaces (SRS-030), timing
requirements (SRS-040, SRS-041), and hardware-dependent fault detection
mechanisms (SAD-031, SAD-032).

Test environment: target hardware board as defined in SRS-072.
  Platform:             <hardware platform name and revision>
  Support equipment:    <oscilloscope, logic analyser, fault injector>
  Calibration records:  <reference>

Test scope:
  - Verify all SW/HW interfaces listed in SAD-062 on target hardware.
  - Measure and confirm worst-case execution times (SRS-040, SAD-052).
  - Verify watchdog refresh and timeout behaviour.
  - Verify memory integrity checks (SAD-032) on real hardware.
  - Verify hardware fault detection and safe-state transition (SAD-031).
  - Verify communication interfaces (SRS-032) with real or simulated
    external systems.

Entry criteria: SW integration tests (Level 2) passed; target hardware
available and verified against hardware specification.

Exit criteria:
  a) All HW-SW integration test cases executed.
  b) All hardware interface requirements (SRS-030) and timing requirements
     (SRS-040, SRS-041) covered and met.
  c) All Critical and Major findings resolved.
  d) Test results reviewed and approved by the Software Verifier (SP-021).
<<<
