[TEST_CASE]
UID: HWIT-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <Watchdog timer: refresh and timeout behaviour>
TEST_TYPE: HW-SW-Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Target hardware is powered and the software is initialised.
- Watchdog timer is enabled and configured to <n> ms timeout.
- System is in normal operating state (safety task executing cyclically).
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Allow software to operate normally for <n> cycles; confirm no watchdog
   timeout occurs and no reset is generated.
2. Using a debug probe or test hook, inhibit the watchdog refresh call in
   the safety task for one cycle.
3. Observe system behaviour for up to <n + margin> ms.
4. Restore normal watchdog refresh; observe recovery behaviour.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- During normal operation: no watchdog-induced reset.
- After one missed refresh: watchdog timeout fires within <n> ms; system
  transitions to safe state (hardware reset or fail-safe output activation).
- Recovery: system re-initialises and enters safe state; a fault log entry
  records the watchdog event.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
<To be completed upon test execution>
<<<
VERDICT: NOT_RUN
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-030
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: HWIT-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: <Digital I/O interface: output command and readback>
TEST_TYPE: HW-SW-Integration
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Target hardware is powered and software is initialised.
- Digital output channel <n> is wired to digital input channel <m>
  via a loopback connection on the test rig.
- Output is in the de-energised (safe) state.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Software commands output channel <n> to the energised state.
2. Read back the state of input channel <m> after <n> ms.
3. Software commands output channel <n> back to the de-energised state.
4. Read back input channel <m> after <n> ms.
5. Disconnect the loopback; allow one execution cycle; check response.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Step 2: input channel <m> reads ENERGISED; no fault logged.
- Step 4: input channel <m> reads DE-ENERGISED; no fault logged.
- Step 5: output-readback mismatch detected within one cycle; fault logged
  with correct code; output commanded to safe (de-energised) state.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
<To be completed upon test execution>
<<<
VERDICT: NOT_RUN
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-030
  ROLE: Verifies

