TITLE: Software architecture and design verification report

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Architecture and Design Verification
Report as required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.3 and Table A.1 (document 14).
It records the outcome of the independent verification of the architecture and
design deliverables produced in sections 2 through 6 before those documents
are baselined and detailed implementation commences.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SAD-090
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
The architecture and design verification shall cover all deliverables
produced in this document:

  a) Software Architecture Specification (section 2):
       - Completeness: all SRS requirements (doc 6) are allocated to one or
         more architectural components.
       - Consistency of the architecture with the SRS.
       - Correct application of Table A.3 and Table A.4 techniques at the
         level required for the target SIL (SAD-030 through SAD-043).
       - Adequacy of data flow (SAD-020), control flow (SAD-021), and
         partitioning (SAD-010) for freedom from interference.

  b) Software Design Specification (section 3):
       - Completeness: a design record exists for each module in SAD-011.
       - Consistency with the architecture.
       - Adequacy of error handling (SAD-033) and timing budgets (SAD-052).

  c) Software Interface Specifications (section 4):
       - All interfaces fully defined per SAD-060.
       - Interface register (SAD-061, SAD-062) complete and consistent with
         the architecture.

  d) Integration Test Specifications (sections 5 and 6):
       - Coverage of all interface requirements (SAD-060 to SAD-062).
       - Adequacy of test strategy and entry/exit criteria.

Verification method: structured inspection using a checklist derived from
EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.3 requirements.
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence — see SP-021>
Checklist reference: <document ID or tool reference>
<<<
